      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/84/5422",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ يَمُوتُ مَا لَهُ مِنْ مَالِهِ\nفَقَالَ لَهُ \"ثُلُثُ مَالِهِ وَ لِلْمَرْأَةِ أَيْضاً\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5422 - Hammad ibn ʿIsa narrated from Shuayb ibn Yaʿqub from Abu Baṣir, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a man who dies - how much of his wealth he can bequeath.\nImam (as) said: \"One-third of his wealth, and the same applies to a woman as well.\""
        ]
      }
    },
